# Hint: Use input() to get numbers and operation
# Handle different arithmetic operations
def simple_calculator():
    pass  # Replace with your implementation

# Uncomment to test your function
# simple_calculator()`} 
                />
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
                <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-300">Solution Hints</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                  <li>Use <code>float(input())</code> for number inputs</li>
                  <li>Handle different operations (+, -, *, /)</li>
                  <li>Implement error handling for invalid inputs</li>
                  <li>Use conditional statements to select operation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </li>
            
            <li>
              <strong>Grade Calculator:</strong> Write a program that takes multiple test scores, calculates the average, and outputs a letter grade.
              <div class="mt-4">
                <CodePlayground 
                  client:load 
                  initialCode={`# Grade Calculator Challenge
